title: A View of the Drawing Room, Cosham House
provenance:
Eugene V. Thaw Collection
 Hazlitt, Gooden & Fox. Ltd., London
medium: Brush and watercolor and graphite on white wove paper
description: This view of a drawing room is presented from the doorway of an adjoining room. Floor-length windows on the right lead out to the veranda and garden below. The furniture, dating to the 1860's, along with the lattice wallpaper, screen, pictures, books and plants, creates a look of organized clutter, typical of the Victorian style of decoration.
name: Drawing
